.Dd July 15, 2026
.Dt MIDIMEND 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm midimend
.Nd mend MIDI between CoreMIDI ports with a JavaScript script
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar config.json
.Nm
.Fl \-measure
.Op Ar config.json
.Nm
.Fl \-list\-devices
.Op Ar config.json
.Nm
.Fl \-init
.Ar script.js
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
connects to MIDI sources, runs a JavaScript processing script per event,
and emits the mended stream on a virtual output port that a DAW uses as
its input.
Scripts use the same JavaScript API as the Scripter MIDI plug-in.
With
.Ql feedback
configured, the virtual output gets a same-named companion port; parameter
feedback a DAW sends there (control-surface LEDs, motor faders) is passed
through to the configured devices.
.Pp
Without arguments,
.Nm
runs the config at
.Pa ~/Music/Midimend/config.json .
Config and script files are watched; saving either hot-reloads the
script.
Changing the config's
.Ql midi
section requires a restart.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Fl
.It Fl \-measure Op Ar config.json
Run normally, additionally printing
.Nm Ns 's
added latency every 10 seconds: percentiles from MIDI driver receipt to
script entry (the queue hop) and to processing done (any resulting events
sent).
.It Fl \-list\-devices Op Ar config.json
Print the MIDI devices currently present.
Given a config, also show which devices its
.Ql hardware
entries match, which are ignored, and which entries match nothing.
.It Fl \-init Ar script.js
Print a config skeleton for the script to stdout, with the defaults from
its
.Ql PluginParameters
filled in.
Script warnings go to stderr, so the JSON can be redirected to a file.
.It Fl h , Fl \-help
Print usage.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Pa
.It Pa ~/Music/Midimend/config.json
Default config, used when
.Nm
is started without arguments (as
.Ql brew services start midimend
does).
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Start a config for a script, then see what is connected:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
midimend --init myscript.js > ~/Music/Midimend/config.json
midimend --list-devices ~/Music/Midimend/config.json
midimend
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
README and script API notes:
.Lk https://github.com/mschuerig/midimend
